Description: 
Businesswoman Deirdre Bounds investigates the ethics of 
the British gold jewellery industry. She challenges retailers 
to reveal where their raw materials are extracted, and 
travels to a mine in Senegal, where a child worker 
provides an insight into the hazardous work he does at an 
illegal site. The former comedienne also explores ways to 
improve the sourcing of gold, looking at Fairtrade, 
Fairmined and recycled products.
